link_preview_attachment.title: Why Market Cap Doesn’t Matter for XRP! 🚀  Most people think XRP can’t reach $10,000 because of market cap—but that’s a myth. Here’s why:  🔹 XRP is built for high-speed transactions, settling in 3-5 seconds. The same XRP can be reused up to 50 times per day, meaning it only needs a fraction of total liquidity to move massive amounts.  🔹 A tokenized global economy is coming—worth $1-2 quadrillion. If XRP even handles 10% of that, daily settlements will be in the trillions, requiring a higher price per token for liquidity efficiency.  🔹 Circulating supply matters. With only 53 billion XRP in use, global adoption by institutions, CBDCs, and governments could drive demand sky-high.  🔥 Market cap doesn’t determine XRP’s value—utility does. The price must rise to meet global liquidity needs.  💬 Do you believe XRP can pass $10,000? XRP isn’t  going to $1000 anytime soon

XRP current market cap is $178 Billion
Bitcoin market cap $1.98 Trillion

Lets do the math, to understand better 
- Current XRP $3 with a Market Cap $1.78 Billion 
- Current Bitcoin Market Cap is $1.98 Trillion 
- 1.98 trillion / 178 Billion = 11.12
- 11.12 X $3 = $33.37

This means that assuming XRP takes 
BTC current place its only going to $33.37 max!
XRP
would need over a 55 Trillion dollar market cap to reach $1000
